List AAGI Palette Colour Combinations

Source: R/aagi_palettes.R
aagi_palettes.Rd

Returns a list of curated palettes of AAGI colours, which includes:

primary

The three primary AAGI colours

secondary

The three secondary support colours in the AAGI colour palette.

full

The full set of all six colours in the AAGI palette

colourful

All colours in the palette minus “AAGI Black”

bright

Four “bright” colours including, “AAGI Bright Green”, “AAGI Blue” and “AAGI Yellow”

bluegreeen

Three blue, green or bluegreen AAGI colours including “AAGI Bright Green”, “AAGI Turquoise”, “AAGI Blue”, “AAGI Green” and “AAGI Bluegreen”

Usage

aagi_palettes()

Value

A list object of AAGI colours grouped by palette combinations

Examples

# View all five palettes' names and hexadecimal colour codes
 aagi_palettes()
#> $primary
#>        AAGI Black AAGI Bright Green    AAGI Turquoise 
#>         "#414042"         "#B6D438"         "#00808b" 
#> 
#> $secondary
#>   AAGI Blue  AAGI Green AAGI Yellow 
#>   "#648FD2"   "#54921E"   "#FFBC42" 
#> 
#> $colourful
#> AAGI Bright Green    AAGI Turquoise         AAGI Blue        AAGI Green 
#>         "#B6D438"         "#00808b"         "#648FD2"         "#54921E" 
#>       AAGI Yellow 
#>         "#FFBC42" 
#> 
#> $full
#>        AAGI Black AAGI Bright Green    AAGI Turquoise         AAGI Blue 
#>         "#414042"         "#B6D438"         "#00808b"         "#648FD2" 
#>        AAGI Green       AAGI Yellow 
#>         "#54921E"         "#FFBC42" 
#> 
#> $bright
#> AAGI Bright Green         AAGI Blue       AAGI Yellow 
#>         "#B6D438"         "#648FD2"         "#FFBC42" 
#> 
#> $bluegreen
#> AAGI Turquoise      AAGI Blue     AAGI Green 
#>      "#00808b"      "#648FD2"      "#54921E" 
#> 
 aagi_palettes()$colourful
#> AAGI Bright Green    AAGI Turquoise         AAGI Blue        AAGI Green 
#>         "#B6D438"         "#00808b"         "#648FD2"         "#54921E" 
#>       AAGI Yellow 
#>         "#FFBC42" 
 aagi_palettes()$bluegreen
#> AAGI Turquoise      AAGI Blue     AAGI Green 
#>      "#00808b"      "#648FD2"      "#54921E"
